Package com.eclipsesource.tabris.push

Interface CloudPush

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.rap.rwt.client.service.ClientService, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CloudPushImpl
    public interface CloudPush
extends org.eclipse.rap.rwt.client.service.ClientService

    CloudPush is a ClientService implementation and can be obtained by calling RWT.getClient().getService( CloudPush.class );. A CloudPush instance can be used to register a client to receive push notifications by simply adding a CloudPushListener. This instructs the client to register itself once at the push service that is common for the client platform.

    After a client is registered to receive notifications the CloudPush service notifies all attached CloudPushListener if a registration, message or error was received.

    After a message was pushed to the client it forwards the message to the server. This message can be obtained by calling getMessage().

    Since:
    1.4
    See Also:
    CloudPushListener
    No Implement:
    This interface is not intended to be implemented by clients.
